    dc:title "Octocorallia (Cnidaria: Anthozoa) from Brazilian reefs" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5207418>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5207420>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5207422> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5207418>
    dc:description "Figure 1. Map of distribution of reef octocorals in different regions off the Brazilian coastline. The Espírito Santo State area (*) includes the Vitória- Trindade seamount chain. “BA Sector” refer to a division of reef areas in Bahia State by Leão (1996)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5207418/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5207420>
    dc:description "Figure 2. Carijoa riisei (Duchassaing and Michelotti, 1860) (MNRJ 00153): (A) colony, (A′) branch. Neospongodes atlantica Kükenthal, 1903 (MNRJ 00335): (B) colony, (B′) branch. Heterogorgia uatumani Castro, 1990 (MNRJ 00504): (C) colony, (C′) branch. Scale bars: A–C, 2 cm;A′–C′, 5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5207420/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5207422>
    dc:description "Figure 3. Sclerites of Carijoa riisei (Duchassaing and Michelotti, 1860) (MNRJ 00385): (A) anthocodia; (B) anthostele, near anthocodia; (C) outer layer of coenenchyme of polyp column (branch); (D) inner layer of polyp column." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5207422/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

